[1] Brazil (Bahia)
Date: Sat 25 Apr 2009
Source: The Irish News [edited]
<http://www.irishnews.com/breaka.asp?tser1=ser&par=bar&storyid=408235>


Brazil's health authorities said the number of known dengue cases in
the northeastern state of Bahia has soared by more than 250 percent
so far this year [2009]. A statement released by the state's health
department said 50 864 dengue cases were registered through 10 Apr
[2009] -- 266 percent more than in the same period last year [2008].

The statement posted on the department's website said that during
this period the disease killed 41 people.

--
Communicated by:
HealthMap Alerts via ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The 23 Apr 2009 edition of ComuniWeb at
<http://www.comuniweb.com.br/?idpaginas=20&idmaterias=502060> (in
Portuguese, posted on ProMED-PORT) reported that dengue has been
registered in 374 municipalities in the state. There have been 352
serious dengue cases (probably DHF), with 41 deaths.

A map of Brazil showing the states can be accessed at
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/americas/brazil.jpg>.
A Health Map/ProMED-mail interactive map of Brazil can be accessed at
<http://healthmap.org/r/008M>. - Mod.TY]

