[5] Society Islands (Tahiti)
Date: Wed 22 Apr 2009
Source: Agence Tahitienne de Presse (Thaitipresse) [in French, trans.
& summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.tahitipresse.pf/index.cfm?snav=see&presse=27313>


The Department of Health and Public Safety provided information that
its officers will carry out a mosquito control operation on 23 Apr
[2009] in 2 districts in Faa'a (Leverd and Tahiti Tuning) following
the identification of 2 new cases of dengue type 4 [virus infection].
To fight against the proliferation of dengue, the Mayor of Faa'a
urged everyone to participate actively in the campaign against the
vector, in particular destroying mosquito breeding sites.

--
